entries.title: Lord Of The Dance creator Michael Flatley has 'aggressive form of cancer'
entries.description: Irish-American dancer Michael Flatley has "an aggressive form of cancer" and has had to undergo surgery, according to a statement on his Instagram account.

entries.title: Tennis star Naomi Osaka announces pregnancy
entries.description: Tennis star Naomi Osaka is pregnant and plans to return to competition in 2024.

entries.title: Russia's Wagner Group claims body found of missing British aid worker in Ukraine
entries.description: Russia's Wagner Group has claimed the body of one of the missing British aid workers in Ukraine has been found.

entries.title: Key questions remain after uranium discovered at Heathrow Airport
entries.description: A major multi-pronged investigation will be under way following the discovery at Heathrow Airport of uranium in a package sent from Pakistan.

entries.title: Iran branded 'barbaric regime' over planned execution of man accused of being UK spy
entries.description: The foreign secretary has condemned the planned execution of a British-Iranian dual national by Iran, calling it "a politically motivated act by a barbaric regime".

entries.title: French Football Federation chief suspended following comments about Zinedine Zidane
entries.description: The president of the French Football Federation (FFF) has been suspended following an extraordinary meeting of the organisation's executive committee.

entries.title: American football player Damar Hamlin who suffered cardiac arrest mid-game is released from hospital
entries.description: American football player Damar Hamlin who collapsed and suffered a cardiac arrest during a game last week has now been released from hospital in Buffalo.

entries.title: Suicide bomb attack kills 20 outside Afghan foreign ministry in Kabul
entries.description: A suicide bomb attack outside the foreign ministry in Afghanistan's capital Kabul has killed at least 20 people and injured many others, the Taliban have said.

entries.title: All flights across US grounded due to computer system glitch - US media
entries.description: All flights across the US have been grounded due to a glitch with the Federal Aviation Administration's computer system, US media reports.

entries.title: German riot police start removing village activists blocking coal mine expansion
entries.description: Riot police have entered a condemned village in Germany to remove protesters attempting to stop it from being demolished to make way for the expansion of a coal mine.

entries.title: Man 'neutralised' by police after attacking several people at Paris train station
entries.description: A man has been "neutralised" after attacking several people at a train station in Paris, a French minister has said.

entries.title: Mother accused of joining Islamic State and keeping woman as a slave
entries.description: A German mother accused of keeping a young Yazidi woman as a slave after travelling to Iraq to join the Islamic State (IS) was due to go on trial today.
